  "conditionals": 39,
  "created": "2025-10-08",
  "description": "The phosphate (Pho) regulon controls the cellular response to phosphate limitation, regulating over 30 genes involved in phosphate scavenging, transport, and metabolism. The two-component system PhoR-PhoB senses periplasmic phosphate levels through the PstSCAB transport complex. Under phosphate starvation, PhoB-P activates expression of alkaline phosphatase, alternative transporters, and phosphate metabolism genes, demonstrating sophisticated nutrient sensing and metabolic adaptation.",
  "id": "ecoli_pho_regulon",
